<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Carter</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hawaiian Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-01-21"><hi rend="italic">January 21,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It is my sad duty to inform you that His
                            Majesty Kalakaua, King of Hawaii, died yesterday at 2:35 p.m., at San
                            Francisco.</p>
                        <p>In this hour of personal grief and anxious solicitude for the welfare of
                            my bereaved country, I must content myself with this simple announcement
                            of the sorrowful event and pray you to communicate it to the
                            President.</p>
                        <p>Please accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. A. P. Carter</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>